{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Rqk9QiZn1b2XA5Z5BtNL51","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So I have 386 entries in c.json, but there are still 216 missing from the actual vendor list. The issue is that I classified 386 entries but many of the keys in c.json don't match the exact vendor names from the Excel. For example:\n- I added \"Allianz Australia Workers\\u2019 Compensation (Victoria) Limited\" (with curly apostrophe U+2019) but the Excel has \"Allianz Australia Workers' Compensation (Victoria) Limited\" (with straight apostrophe U+0027)\n- I added \"Catering Iviä\\u0087 D.O.O.\" but the Excel has \"Catering Iviä‡ D.O.O.\" (different representation)\n\n\nThe encoding mismatches are preventing my keys from aligning with the Excel names, so I need to use the exact string representations from the source file. I'm looking at the 216 unclassified vendors and noticing a pattern with mojibake entries—names that got corrupted during encoding conversion—so I'll need to process these in batches to add them all correctly. I'm extracting the exact vendor names from the output, paying careful attention to the character encoding issues—these mojibake strings need to be captured precisely as they appear, including the special characters and encoding artifacts, so I can map them correctly to the vendor list. Writing a Python script to extract and merge vendor data...\n\nI'm setting up a classification system based on vendor name patterns—Croatian legal entities like D.O.O. get marked as Terminate with Facilities/Internal Operations at LOW priority, while hotels and restaurants also get Terminate/Facilities/LOW. Insurance companies and law firms map to Consolidate with HR or Legal at MEDIUM, government agencies go to Terminate/Optimize with Legal, and recruitment firms are Terminate/HR/LOW.\n\nWriting the classification script...","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3390,"cache_read_input_tokens":45645,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":3390,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"48836790-c43b-4514-99d0-96fcf694e6a4","uuid":"b62a5011-aa79-4f93-9475-d8c56138af68"}
